  <!-- FAQ -->
  <section style="margin-top: 3rem;">
    <h2 style="font-family:'Lora',serif;font-size:1.6rem;font-weight:700;color:#111827;margin-bottom:1rem;">Frequently
      Asked Questions</h2>
    <div style="border-bottom:1px solid #e5e7eb;padding:1.25rem 0;">
      <h3 style="font-size:1rem;font-weight:600;color:#111827;margin:0 0 0.5rem;font-family:'DM Sans',sans-serif;">How
        long does it take to set up renewal email automation?</h3>
      <p style="margin:0;color:#4b5563;font-size:0.95rem;line-height:1.7;">Most teams are live with their first active
        sequence in under 7 days. CRM connections are OAuth-based and take minutes. Sequence logic configuration
        typically takes 1–2 hours using a visual builder with pre-built templates.</p>
    </div>
    <div style="border-bottom:1px solid #e5e7eb;padding:1.25rem 0;">
      <h3 style="font-size:1rem;font-weight:600;color:#111827;margin:0 0 0.5rem;font-family:'DM Sans',sans-serif;">Do
        AI-drafted renewal emails actually sound personal?</h3>
      <p style="margin:0;color:#4b5563;font-size:0.95rem;line-height:1.7;">Yes — because they are generated from real
        account context: usage data, support history, specific features adopted, and prior email threads. The quality is
        markedly different from merge-field templates. That said, every draft is reviewed and approved by a CSM before
        sending, which keeps quality high.</p>
    </div>
    <div style="border-bottom:1px solid #e5e7eb;padding:1.25rem 0;">
      <h3 style="font-size:1rem;font-weight:600;color:#111827;margin:0 0 0.5rem;font-family:'DM Sans',sans-serif;">What
        happens if a customer replies to an automated sequence email?</h3>
      <p style="margin:0;color:#4b5563;font-size:0.95rem;line-height:1.7;">The sequence pauses immediately via IMAP
        monitoring and the assigned CSM receives a Slack alert. No further automated emails are sent until the CSM
        manually resumes or closes the sequence. This prevents the common failure of customers receiving follow-ups
        after they've already replied.</p>
    </div>
    <div style="border-bottom:1px solid #e5e7eb;padding:1.25rem 0;">
      <h3 style="font-size:1rem;font-weight:600;color:#111827;margin:0 0 0.5rem;font-family:'DM Sans',sans-serif;">Can
        we use different sequences for different account tiers?</h3>
      <p style="margin:0;color:#4b5563;font-size:0.95rem;line-height:1.7;">Yes. Most teams build 2–3 sequences segmented
        by ARR tier or health score bracket. Enterprise accounts ($100K+) get a more intensive sequence with executive
        escalation steps; SMB accounts get a lighter-touch automated flow. Accounts can also be moved between sequences
        manually as their situation changes.</p>
    </div>
    <div style="padding:1.25rem 0;">
      <h3 style="font-size:1rem;font-weight:600;color:#111827;margin:0 0 0.5rem;font-family:'DM Sans',sans-serif;">Is
        renewal automation only useful for annual contracts?</h3>
      <p style="margin:0;color:#4b5563;font-size:0.95rem;line-height:1.7;">No. The same health scoring and outreach
        logic applies to monthly contracts, multi-year renewals, and usage-based billing milestones. The trigger windows
        adjust — monthly contracts start intervention earlier on health signals rather than calendar dates — but the
        core automation layer works across billing models.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

